settings->about phone:
   VS910 4G
   android 2.2.2
   VS910ZV4

to use android debug bridge:
    settings->applications->Unknown Sources
    settings->applications->Development-> USB debugging
    settings->connectivity->Default connection mode->internet
    settings->wireless&..->Mobile network settings->Select system->LTE/CDMA


root/root.sh
    root and install superuser
    run script from root/ 

bootloader/changeBootloader.sh
    change bootloader to clockwork mod
    run script from bootloader/ 
    **CHECK md5sum**
       or use RevoToolkit to check before rebooting
   
images/uploadStock.sh
    push stock_revo to sdcard so it can be seen by clockwork mod recovery

clockwork mod recovery:
   wipe all cache/wipe all data or settings->privacy->reset (unnecessary?) 
   restore->stock_revo
   

root/root.sh again


bootloader/changeBootloader.sh again
   but with BL = stock bootloader
   **CHECK sums or use RevoToolkit**

root/unroot.sh
   remove root


Get OTA (Over The Air?) updates
    settings->About Phone->Software Updates->Check



root/root.sh again
bootloader/changeBootloader.sh again
upload Gingervolt image
"restore" to Gingervolt



